{"parse":{"title":"garlic","pageid":36576,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"==English==\n[[Image:Garlic.jpg|thumb|Garlic bulbs.]]\n{{wikispecies|Allium sativum}}\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|en|garlick|garlicke||obsolete}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{inh+|en|enm|garlek}}, {{m|enm|garlik}}, from {{inh|en|ang|gārlēac|t=garlic|lit=spear-leek}}, from {{m|ang|gār}} {{gl|\"spear\"; in reference to its sharp, tapering leaves}} + {{m|ang|lēac|t=leek}}. Cognate with {{cog|sco|garlic|t=garlic}}, {{cog|fo|geirleykur|t=garlic}}, {{cog|is|geirlaukur|t=garlic}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈɡɑːlɪk/|a=UK}}\n* {{enPR|gärˈlĭk|a=US}}, {{IPA|en|/ˈɡɑɹlɪk/}}\n* {{audio|en|En-uk-garlic.ogg|a=UK}}\n* {{rhymes|en|ɑː(ɹ)lɪk|s=2}}\n* {{homophones|en|garlick#Etymology_2}}\n*[[w:IPA|IPA]] /'gɑː(r)lɪk/\n*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]] /'gA:(r)lIk/\n{{rfap|en|American English}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun|~}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|Q23400}}A plant, {{taxfmt|Allium sativum|species}}, related to the [[onion]], having a pungent [[bulb]] much used in cooking.\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=2013-03|author=David S. Senchina|title=Athletics and Herbal Supplements|volume=101|issue=2|page=134|magazine=w:American Scientist|url=http://www.americanscientist.org/issues/feature/2013/2/athletics-and-herbal-supplements|text=Athletes' use of herbal supplements has skyrocketed in the past two decades. At the top of the list of popular herbs are echinacea and ginseng, whereas '''garlic''', St. John's wort, soybean, ephedra and others are also surging in popularity or have been historically prevalent.| accessdate=10 May 2013| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130516202757/http://www.americanscientist.org/issues/feature/2013/2/athletics-and-herbal-supplements| archivedate=16 May 2013}}\n# {{senseid|en|Q21546392}}{{lb|en|uncountable}} A preparation from {{taxfmt|Allium sativum|species}} used as a food ingredient or the flavor or other characteristics of such an ingredient.\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col4|en|title=terms derived from the noun ''garlic''|{{l|en|bear's garlic}}, [[bear garlic]] ({{taxfmt|Allium ursinum|species}})|black garlic|{{vern|broadleaf garlic}}, {{l|en|broad-leaved garlic}} ({{taxfmt|Allium ursinum|species}})\n|[[Canadian garlic]] ({{taxlink|Allium canadense|species}})||clove of garlic|{{vern|crow garlic}} ({{taxfmt|Allium vineale|species}})\n|{{vern|daffodil garlic}} ({{taxlink|Allium neapolitanum|species}})\n|{{l|en|elephant garlic}} ({{taxlink|Allium ampeloprasum var. ampeloprasum|variety}})\n|{{vern|false garlic}} ({{taxlink|Nothoscordum bivalve|species}})|[[field garlic]] ({{taxfmt|Allium vineale|species}})\n|garlic bread|garlic butter\n|garlic chewer|{{l|en|garlic chive}} ({{taxfmt|Allium tuberosum|species}})|garlic clove|garlic crusher\n|garlic fingers\n|{{vern|garlic-germander}} ({{taxlink|Teucrium scordium|species}})\n|garlic knot|garlicky\n|garlicless|garliclike\n|garlicmonger|{{l|en|garlic mustard}} ({{taxfmt|Alliaria petiolata|species}})\n|garlic pear,{{vern|garlic-pear}}, {{vern|garlic-peartree}} ({{taxlink|Crataeva gynandra|species}})|garlic powder|garlic press\n|{{vern|garlic root}} ({{taxfmt|Alliaria petiolata|species}})\n|{{vern|garlic-sage}}|garlic salt|garlic sausage|garlic scroll\n|{{vern|garlic toad}} ({{taxlink|Pelobates fuscus|species}})|{{vern|garlic treaclewort}}|{{vern|garlic-tree}} ({{taxlink|Scorodophloeus zenkeri|species}})|garlic soup\n|{{l|en|garlic vine}} ({{taxlink|Mansoa alliacea|species}})\n|[[garlicwort]] ({{taxfmt|Alliaria petiolata|species}})\n|garlion|{{vern|giant garlic}} ({{taxlink|Allium scorodoprasum|species}})|{{vern|golden garlic}} ({{taxlink|Allium moly|species}})\n|{{vern|hard-necked garlic}} ({{taxlink|Allium sativum var. ophioscorodon|variety}})|{{l|en|hedge garlic}} ({{taxfmt|Alliaria petiolata|species}})|[[hog's garlic]] ({{taxfmt|Allium ursinum|species}})\n|{{vern|Italian garlic}} ({{taxlink|Allium pendulinum|species}})\n|jarlic| rosy garlic\n|{{vern|keeled garlic}} ({{taxlink|Allium carinatum|species}})\n|{{vern|Levant garlic}} ({{taxfmt|Allium ampeloprasum|species}})\n|[[meadow garlic]] ({{taxlink|Allium canadense|species}})\n|{{vern|Naples garlic}},{{vern|Neapolitan garlic}} ({{taxlink|Allium neopolitanum|species}})\n|{{vern|Oriental garlic}} ({{taxfmt|Allium tuberosum|species}})\n|peel-garlic,pilgarlick,pilled-garlic\n|society garlic|{{vern|Spanish garlic}} ({{taxlink|Allium scorodoprasum|species}})|{{vern|stag's garlic}} ({{taxfmt|Allium vineale|species}})|garlic toast\n|{{vern|white garlic}} ({{taxlink|Allium neapolitanum|species}})|{{l|en|wild garlic}} ({{taxfmt|Allium ursinum|species}}; {{taxfmt|Allium vineale|species}})|{{l|en|wood garlic}} ({{taxfmt|Allium ursinum|species}})}}\n\n====Related terms====\n* {{l|en|leek}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|plant}}\n* Afrikaans: {{t+|af|knoffel}}\n* Akkadian: {{t|akk|𒋧|tr=šūmū}}\n* Alabama: {{t|akz|kosòoma}}\n* Albanian: {{t+|sq|hudhër|m}}\n* Altai:\n*: Northern Altai: {{t|atv|шарымсак}}\n*: Southern Altai: {{t|alt|сарымсак}}\n* Amharic: {{t|am|ነጭ ሽንኩርት}}\n* Andi: {{t|ani|ражи}}\n* Arabic: {{t|ar|ثُوم|m}}, {{t|ar|ثُومَة|f}} {{qualifier|[[singulative]]}}\n*: Egyptian Arabic: {{t|arz|توم|m|tr=tōm}}\n*: Hijazi Arabic: {{t|acw|ثوم|m|tr=tūm}}\n*: South Levantine Arabic: {{t|ajp|تومة|m|tr=tōme, tōma}}\n* Aragonese: {{t|an|allo}}\n* Aramaic:\n*: Classical Syriac: {{t|syc|ܬܘܡܐ|m|tr=tūmā}}\n* Archi: {{t|aqc|лачи}}\n* Armenian: {{t+|hy|սխտոր}}\n* Aromanian: {{t|rup|alj|n}}, {{t|rup|aljiu|n}}\n* Assamese: {{t|as|নহৰু}}\n* Asturian: {{t+|ast|ayu|m}}\n* Atayal: {{t|tay|niniku}}\n* Avar: {{t|av|ражи}}\n* Avestan: {{t|ae|𐬎𐬭𐬎𐬎𐬁𐬯𐬥𐬁}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{t+|az|sarımsaq}}\n* Bashkir: {{t|ba|һарымһаҡ}}\n* Basque: {{t|eu|baratxuri}}\n* Belarusian: {{t|be|часно́к|m}}, {{t|be|часны́к|m}}\n* Bengali: {{t+|bn|রসুন}}\n* Bikol:\n*: Central Bikol: {{t+|bcl|bawang}}\n* Bouyei: {{t|pcc|hol}}, {{t|pcc|golsois}}\n* Breton: {{t+|br|kignen|m}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|че́сън|m}}, {{q|dialectal}} {{t|bg|чесно́в лук|m}}\n* Bunun: {{t|bnn|vasalu}}\n* Burmese: {{t+|my|ကြက်သွန်ဖြူ}}\n* Carpathian Rusyn: {{t|rue|цибу́ля|f}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|all|m}}\n* Cebuano: {{t|ceb|ahos}}\n* Cherokee: {{t|chr|ᏃᏳᏟ}}\n* Chichewa: {{t|ny|adyo}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Cantonese: {{t|yue|蒜頭|tr=syun3 tau4}}\n*: Dungan: {{t|dng|суан}}, {{t|dng|суантэ}}\n*: Hokkien: {{t+|nan-hbl|蒜頭|tr=soàn-thâu / sǹg-thâu}}\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|大蒜|tr=dàsuàn}}, {{t+|cmn|蒜頭|tr=suàntóu}}\n*: Wu: {{t|wuu|蒜}}\n* Chuvash: {{t|cv|ыхра}}\n* Circassian:\n*: West Circassian: {{t|ady|бжьыныф}}\n* Comorian:\n*: Ngazidja Comorian: {{t|zdj|itrungu thwaumu}}\n* Coptic:\n*: Bohairic Coptic: {{t|cop|ϣϭⲏⲛ}}\n*: Oxyrhynchite Coptic: {{t|cop|ⳉϫⲁⲛ}}\n*: Sahidic Coptic: {{t|cop|ϣϫⲏⲛ|}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|česnek|m}}, {{t|cs|knobloch|m}}\n* Dalmatian: {{t|dlm|ail}}\n* Danish: {{t+|da|hvidløg|n}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|knoflook|m|f}}\n* Dzongkha: {{t|dz|སྐྱ་སྒོགཔ}}\n* Egyptian: {{t|egy|ḫṯn}}\n* Elfdalian: {{t|ovd|waitlok|m}}\n* Esperanto: {{t+|eo|ajlo}}\n* Estonian: {{t+|et|küüslauk}}\n* Faroese: {{t|fo|hvítleykur|m}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|kynsilaukka}} {{qualifier|plant}}; {{t+|fi|valkosipuli}} {{qualifier|plant or bulb}}\n* Flemish:\n*: West Flemish: {{t|vls|look|m}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|ail|m}}\n* Frisian:\n*: West Frisian: {{t|fy|knyflok|n}}\n* Friulian: {{t|fur|ai|m}}\n* Gagauz: {{t|gag|sarmısak}}\n* Galician: {{t+|gl|allo}}\n* Georgian: {{t|ka|ნიორი}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Knoblauch|m}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|σκόρδο|n}}\n*: Ancient Greek: {{t|grc|σκόροδον|n}}, {{qualifier|Koine}} {{t|grc|σκόρδον|n}}\n* Greenlandic: {{t|kl|hvidløgi}}\n* Guarani:\n*: Paraguayan Guarani: {{t-check|gug|sevoiry}}\n* Gujarati: {{t+|gu|લસણ}}\n* Haitian Creole: {{t|ht|lay}}\n* Hausa: {{t|ha|àlbásà mai go}}\n* Hawaiian: {{t|haw|ʻakaʻakai pilau}}, {{t|haw|ʻakaʻakai pūpū}}, {{t|haw|kālika}}\n* Hebrew: {{t+|he|שׁוּם|m|tr=shum}}\n* Higaonon: {{t|mba|lansuna}}\n* Hindi: {{t+|hi|लहसुन|m}}\n* Hmong:\n*: White Hmong: {{t|mww|qej}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|fokhagyma}}\n* Hunsrik: {{t|hrx|Knuwloch|m}}\n* Icelandic: {{t+|is|hvítlaukur}}, {{t|is|g