ᠮᠰᠠᠭ}}\n* Nahuatl: {{t|nah|caxtīllān xonacatl}}\n* Navajo: {{t|nv|tłʼohchin díchʼííʼí}}\n* Neapolitan: {{t|nap|àglio}}\n* Nepali: {{t|ne|लसुन}}\n* Norman: {{t|nrf|ail|m}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{t+|nb|hvitløk|m}}\n*: Nynorsk: {{t|nn|kvitlauk|m}}\n* Occitan: {{t+|oc|alh|m}}\n* Okinawan: {{t|ryu|蒜}}, {{t|ryu|葫|tr=ひる, hiru}}\n* Old East Slavic: {{t|orv|чеснокъ|m}}\n* Old Norse: {{t|non|geirlaukr|m}}\n* Oromo: {{t|om|qullubbii}}\n* Ossetian: {{t|os|нуры}}\n* Pannonian Rusyn: {{t|rsk|цеснок|m}}\n* Papiamentu: {{t|pap|konofló}}\n* Pashto: {{t+|ps|هوږه|f|tr=húẓa}}, {{t|ps|اوږه|f|tr=oẓá}}\n* Persian:\n*: Dari: {{t+|prs|سیر}}\n*: Iranian Persian: {{t+|fa-ira|سیر}}\n* Piedmontese: {{t|pms|ai}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|czosnek|m}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|alho|m}}\n* Punjabi:\n*: Gurmukhi: {{t+|pa|ਥੋਮ|m}}, {{t|pa|ਲਸਣ|m}}\n*: Shahmukhi: {{t|pa|تھوم|m}}, {{t|pa|لَسَݨ|m}}\n* Quechua: {{t|qu|ananisikim}}\n* Romagnol: {{t|rgn|àj|m}}, {{t|rgn|ài|m}}\n* Romani: {{t|rom|sir|m}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|usturoi|m}}, {{t+|ro|ai}}\n* Romansh: {{t|rm|agl|m}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|чесно́к|m}}\n* Sami:\n*: Northern Sami: {{t|se|vilgeslávki}}\n* Sanskrit: {{t+|sa|लशुन|n}}\n* Sardinian:\n*: Campidanese: {{t|sc|allu}}\n* Scots: {{t|sco|garlic}}, {{t|sco|ramps}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{t|gd|creamh|m}}, {{t|gd|gairleag|f}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t+|sh|чѐшња̄к|m}}, {{t+|sh|бели лук|m}}, {{t|sh|бијели лук|m}}\n*: Latin: {{t+|sh|čèšnjāk|m}}, {{t+|sh|beli luk|m}}, {{t+|sh|bijeli luk|m}}\n* Shan: {{t|shn|ၽၵ်းမီႇႁေႃ}}, {{t|shn|မီႇၽိူၵ်ႇၶၢဝ်}}\n* Sherpa: {{t|xsr|སྒོག་པ}}\n* Sicilian: {{t+|scn|agghiu|m}}\n* Sinhalese: {{t|si|සුදු ලූනු}}, {{t|si|සුදුළූණු}}\n* Slovak: {{t+|sk|cesnak|m}}\n* Slovene: {{t+|sl|česen|m}}\n* Somali: {{t+|so|toon|m}}\n* Sorbian:\n*: Lower Sorbian: {{t|dsb|kobołk|m}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|ajo|m}}\n* Svan: {{t|sva|ნიუ̂რა}}\n* Swahili: {{t|sw|kitunguu saumu}}, {{t|sw|somu}}, {{t|sw|thumu}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|vitlök|c}}\n* Sylheti: {{t|syl|ꠞꠃꠘ}}\n* Tagalog: {{t|tl|bawang}}\n* Tajik: {{t+|tg|сир}}, {{t+|tg|сирпиёз}}\n* Tamil: {{t+|ta|பூண்டு}}\n* Tatar: {{t+|tt|сарымсак}}\n* Telugu: {{t+|te|వెల్లుల్లి}}, {{t+|te|తెల్లగడ్డ}}, {{t|te|ఎల్లిగడ్డ}}, {{t|te|లశునము}}\n* Thai: {{t+|th|กระเทียม}}\n*: Northern Thai: {{t-needed|nod}}\n*: Phu Thai: {{t-needed|pht}}\n*: Southern Thai: {{t-needed|sou}}\n* Tibetan: {{t|bo|སྒོག་པ}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|sarımsak}}\n* Turkmen: {{t|tk|sarymsak}}\n* Udmurt: {{t-needed|udm}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t|uk|часни́к|m}}, {{t|uk|чосни́к|m}} {{qualifier|rare}}\n* Unami: {{t|unm|ulepën}}\n* Urdu: {{t|ur|لَہْسَن|m}}\n* Uyghur: {{t+|ug|سامساق}}\n* Uzbek: {{t+|uz|sarimsoq}}\n* Venetan: {{t+|vec|ajo|m}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t+|vi|tỏi}}\n* Vilamovian: {{t|wym|knöwłoch}}\n* Volapük: {{t|vo|läl}}\n* Waigali: {{t|wbk|ṭüm}}\n* Welsh: {{t+|cy|garlleg|m}}, {{t|cy|craf|m-p}}\n* Xhosa: {{t|xh|ivimbampunzi}}\n* Yakut: {{t|sah|чочунаах}}\n* Yiddish: {{t|yi|קנאָבל}}\n* Yoron: {{t|yox|蒜}}, {{t|yox|葫|tr=ぴる, piru}}\n* Yoruba: {{t|yo|ayù}}\n* Zazaki: {{t+|zza|sir|m}}\n* Zhuang: {{t|za|ho}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{en-verb|~s|~king|~ked}}\n\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[flavor]] with garlic.\n#* {{RQ:Pynchon Crying of Lot 49|year=1976|page=2|chapter=1|passage={{...}}then through the sunned gathering of her marjoram and sweet basil from the herb garden, reading of book reviews in the latest ''Scientific American'', into the layering of a lasagna, '''garlicking''' of a bread, tearing up of romaine leaves, eventually, oven on, into the mixing of the twilight's whisky sours against the arrival of her husband, Wendell (“Mucho) Maas from work, she wondered, wondered, shuffling back through a fat deckful of days which seemed (wouldn't she be first to admit it?) more or less identical, or all pointing the same way subtly like a conjurer's deck, any odd one readily clear to a trained eye.}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|to flavour with garlic}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|allejar}}\n* Finnish: {{t|fi|[[maustaa]] [[valkosipulilla]]}}\n* Polish: {{t|pl|[[dodawać]] [[czosnek|czosnku]]|impf}}, {{t|pl|[[dodać]] [[czosnek|czosnku]]|pf}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===See also===\n* {{l|en|alliaceous}}\n* {{l|en|clove#Etymology 2|clove}}\n* {{l|en|ramp}}, {{l|en|ramson}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{pedia}}\n* {{comcatlite}}\n\n{{C|en|Alliums|Spices and herbs|Vegetables|Root vegetables}}\n\n==Middle English==\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|enm|noun|altform=1}} \n\n# {{alt form|enm|garlek}}"}}